 explaining the many ways in which insects avoid becoming a meal for a predator, and the ways in which predators evade their defensive strategies, Gilbert Waldbauer conveys an essential understanding of the unrelenting coevolutionary forces at work in the world around us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aInsectsxDefenses. 0aInsectsxPredators of. 7aNATURE / Animals.2bisacsh  abooks about bugs.  abooks for kids and adults.  abooks for my grandson.  abug camouflage.  abug defensive mechanisms.  acool bugs.  adistraction for kids.  aeasy to read.  aecology.  aengaging.  aentomology.  aevolution.  afood chain explained.  afood chain of bugs.  afun books.  afun facts about bugs.  agifts for kids.  agreat for reluctant readers.  ahow bugs survive.  ainformative books.  ainsects.  ainvertebrates zoology.  alearning while reading.  aman vs beast.  apredator and prey.  ascience and math.  asurvival techniques of bugs.  awhat eats bugs.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026912540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095246140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520952461423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520952461/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY